SIMPLE: requisite
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Requisite
<hw>Req"ui*site</hw> <pr>(r?k"w?-z?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That
which is required, or is necessary; something indispensable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God, on his part, has declared the <qex>requisites</qex> on ours;
what we must do to obtain blessings, is the great business of us all to
know.</q> <rj><qau>Wake.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Requisite</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Requisite
<hw>Req"ui*site</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>requisitus</ets>, p.
p. <ets>requirere</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>quaerere</ets>
to ask. See <er>Require</er>.]</ety> <def>Required by the nature of
things, or by circumstances; so needful that it can not be dispensed
with; necessary; indispensable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All truth <qex>requisite</qex> for men to know.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Necessary; needful; indispensable;
essential.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Req"ui*site*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Req"ui*site*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Requisition</ent>⟦br⟧
